reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Thrilled with this chair
reviews.reviewText: I sit for many hours a day working , and this chair is absolutely perfect . Easy assembly and insanely comfortable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Superior support, value, and style
reviews.reviewText: A valued and discriminating friend had sat in every chair in an office box store. This chair was his pick, and when I tried his, I was very happy - It even adjusted for my 5'2" frame. This seller had a better price than the box store, and I love my new chair! I am sitting at a computer teaching from home, and this chair corrected sciatic irritation. I was pleased to see so few parts to assemble and the superior packaging. My only challenge was needing a second pair of hands due to the wonderful "cush" surrounding the bolt holes. I found no problem with the holes themselves.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars An Attractive Addition to My Home Office
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice looking piece of office furniture. Assembly was a bit of a pain because it was difficult to get some of the bolts started, especially for the connection of the seat back to the chair arms. I had to use a lot of care not to strip any of the bolts because I couldn't see where/how exactly they were lining up with the pre-drilled holes. It just took a little longer than I thought it would. Chair comfort is just okay. Curiously, the chair is nicely cushioned everywhere except for where my butt settles. The design should have more padding there and it would be perfect. As is, four stars seems an accurate overall rating.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very nice and comfortable chair, highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Don't waste your money--this is a piece of crap
reviews.reviewText: This chair was ridiculous to put together--there was a screw hole in the side that was 75% covered so we had to purchase our own screw that was longer than the screws supplied with the chair in order to make it work. This was after calling "customer support" and being told that we'd have to try to return it, but since we bought it from an amazon vendor, they were wanting us to pay for the return shipping, which we weren't willing to do. The chair makes tons of noises (squeaking whenever you move) and every third time or so that I go to sit in it, it lowers itself all the way down, so I have to readjust the height. Really a big waste of money.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable office chair
reviews.reviewText: Poitives: Great value for the price. Comfortable office chair for 8+ hrs day. Sure, a $1k chair may be more satisfying, but for $130 I don't think it can be beat. Way more comfortable and ergonomic to me than gaming chairs.Good height adjust for most common 27-30" desks. Chair is able to lean back slightly, which I love. 7 months from initial purchase, 40+ hours a week, it still functions and looks like new (including the "leather" covering).Cons: It can be a major pain to put together (arms especially) but is doable, even solo. I must have forgot that caveat as 7 months from initial purchase, I just recieved and built my second chair for a home office. Again, it's a pain, but you only build it once so I went for it. Chair can also get noisier as it breaks in (creaky), but again, price to performance I'm not going to complain.
